transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, Quinn speaking, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I just wanted to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: Okay, one moment.

Speaker 2: Your name, John?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: Alrighty, John, I do see that you are a VIP with us here.

Speaker 1: Do you mind if I ask why you're canceling?

Speaker 2: I just have too many, man.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay.

Speaker 2: I have too much.

Speaker 1: As soon as when I'm done with what I have, I'll re-prescribe.

Speaker 2: Well, yeah, so basically you wouldn't even need to cancel.

Speaker 1: We could just give you like five months where you're not being billed or charged anything.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, why don't you do that?

Speaker 1: And if I need to renew it sooner, I'll renew it sooner.

Speaker 2: Call at any moment, correct.

Speaker 1: Okay, that works for me.

Speaker 2: Alrighty, well, I just did that for you, sir.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: Have a good day.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
